          <h2 id="_1">算法概要</h2>
<h3 id="_2">问题定义</h3>
<p>假设:  </p>
<ul>
<li>Square Matrix <mathjax>$ \mathcal{A} $</mathjax> has dimension <mathjax>$ I\times I $</mathjax> with elements <mathjax>$ a(i,k) $</mathjax> for <mathjax>$ 0\leq i&lt;I $</mathjax> and <mathjax>$ 0\leq k&lt;I $</mathjax>.</li>
<li>Column Vector <mathjax>$ \mathcal{B} $</mathjax> has dimension <mathjax>$ I\times 1 $</mathjax> with elements <mathjax>$ b(k,0) $</mathjax> for <mathjax>$ 0\leq k&lt;I $</mathjax>.</li>
</ul>
<p>We then find:</p>
<ul>
<li>Column Vector <mathjax>$ \mathcal{C}=\mathcal{A}\times\mathcal{B} $</mathjax> has dimension <mathjax>$ I\times 1 $</mathjax> with elements <mathjax>$ c(i,0) $</mathjax> defined as: <mathjax>$ c(i,0)=\sum\limits_{k=0}^{I-1} a(i,k)*b(k,0) $</mathjax>.</li>
<li>We split <mathjax>$ \mathcal{A} $</mathjax> and <mathjax>$ \mathcal{B} $</mathjax> into blocks (sub-matrices) small enough so that a pair of blocks can be multiplied in memory on a single node in the cluster and the computation only includes one phase \textbf{MapReduce}.</li>
</ul>
<p>Notation:</p>
<ul>
<li><mathjax>$ I $</mathjax>: the dimension of square matrix or column vector.</li>
<li><mathjax>$ \mathcal{A}=a(i,k)\in\mathbb{R}^{I\times I} $</mathjax>: square matrix</li>
<li><mathjax>$ \mathcal{B}=b(k,0)\in\mathbb{R}^{I\times 1} $</mathjax>: column vector.</li>
<li><mathjax>$ \mathcal{C}=c(i,0)\in\mathbb{R}^{I\times 1} $</mathjax>: column vector.</li>
<li><mathjax>$ IB $</mathjax>: the number of rows per <mathjax>$ \mathcal{A} $</mathjax> block and <mathjax>$ \mathcal{C} $</mathjax> block.</li>
<li><mathjax>$ KB $</mathjax>: the number of columns per <mathjax>$ \mathcal{A} $</mathjax> block.</li>
<li><mathjax>$ NIB $</mathjax>: the number of <mathjax>$ \mathcal{A} $</mathjax> row and <mathjax>$ \mathcal{C} $</mathjax> row partitions = <mathjax>$ \frac{I-1}{IB}+1 $</mathjax>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="example">Example</h3>
<ul>
<li>Naive Method: <mathjax>$$ \begin{bmatrix} 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 3 &amp; 4\\ 2 &amp; 3 &amp; 4 &amp; 1\\ 3 &amp; 4 &amp; 1 &amp; 2\\ 4 &amp; 3 &amp; 2 &amp; 1\\\end{bmatrix}\times \begin{bmatrix}1\\3\\2\\4\end{bmatrix} =\begin{bmatrix}29\\23\\25\\21 \end{bmatrix} $$</mathjax></li>
<li>Block Strategy: <mathjax>$$ \left[\begin{array}{cc|cc}1 &amp; 2 &amp; 3 &amp; 4\\2 &amp; 3 &amp; 4 &amp; 1\\\hline3 &amp; 4 &amp; 1 &amp; 2\\ 4 &amp; 3 &amp; 2 &amp; 1\\\end{array}\right]\times
    \left[\begin{array}{c}1\\3\\\hline2\\4\end{array}\right]=
    \left[\begin{array}{c}7\\11\\\hline 15\\13\end{array}\right]+
    \left[\begin{array}{c}22\\12\\\hline 10\\8\end{array}\right]=
    \left[\begin{array}{c}29\\23\\\hline 25\\21\end{array}\right] $$</mathjax></li>
</ul>
